						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged. It is dated in the 31st year of an unspecified king. The names of the signatories at the end make it probable that king Kulōttuṅga-Chōḷa III is meant. The inscription registers an <hi rend="italic">uḷvari</hi> for a tax free <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land situated in Vīrarājēndra-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, which was granted to the temple for the requirements of daily worship etc.</p>						

						</summary>
